As of the [[2020 United States Census|2020 census]], the population of Mount Carmel was 5,725, continuing a long decline from its peak of 17,967 in 1930. According to the 2019–2023 American Community Survey five-year estimates — which use a different methodology than the decennial census and may vary slightly in totals — the median household income was $52,667 and the per capita income was $27,065. Approximately 16.2% of residents lived below the poverty line. The racial composition of the borough was approximately 90.9%&nbsp;White, 4.6%&nbsp;Hispanic or Latino, and 2.8%&nbsp;two or more races. The median age was 42.5&nbsp;years.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=Mount+Carmel+borough,+Pennsylvania |title=Explore Census Data |publisher=United States Census Bureau |access-date=May 4, 2026}}</ref>

